# CODEOWNERS – define who must review changes to sensitive areas
#
# SSDLC principle: mandatory code review for security-critical files.
# GitHub enforces these reviews before a PR can be merged.
#
# Format: <pattern>  <owner> [<owner> …]
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Security configuration – security team must review any changes
.github/workflows/           @Pelino-Courses/security
.github/dependabot.yml       @Pelino-Courses/security
SECURITY.md                  @Pelino-Courses/security
config.py                    @Pelino-Courses/security

# Core application – any change to the auth layer requires review
app/auth.py                  @Pelino-Courses/security @Pelino-Courses/developers
app/models.py                @Pelino-Courses/security @Pelino-Courses/developers

# Everything else – any repo member can review
*                            @Pelino-Courses/developers
